article.headline: Lane hits go-ahead 3-pointer with 1.5 seconds left, Georgia State beats Coastal Carolina 72-71
article.description: — Toneari Lane scored 16 points, including a 3-pointer from the corner with 1.5 seconds left, to help Georgia State defeat Coastal Carolina 72-71 on Wednesday night.

article.story: ATLANTA -- — Toneari Lane scored 16 points, including a 3-pointer from the corner with 1.5 seconds left, to help Georgia State defeat Coastal Carolina 72-71 on Wednesday night. Dwon Odom drove into the lane, drawing the attention of all five defenders, and found Lane wide open in the corner for the winning shot. Lane was 5 of 14 shooting (4 for 9 from 3-point range) for the Panthers (13-14, 7-8 Sun Belt Conference). Lucas Taylor was 5 of 18 shooting and went 5 for 6 from the line to add 15 points. Odom finished 6 of 9 from the field to finish with 14 points. The Chanticleers (8-18, 5-10) were led by Jacob Meyer, who recorded 23 points and nine rebounds. Kylan Blackmon added 11 points for Coastal Carolina. Kevin Easley Jr. also had 10 points and eight rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
